    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter April 30 with a high-ceiling core, anchored by **Yordan Alvarez** (87.42) and **Trea Turner** (72.20). **Yordan Alvarez** remains our premier start; he benefits from a pristine matchup against Young, with park factors and a favorable spot in the two-hole boosting his efficiency score to near-elite levels. Meanwhile, **Trea Turner** remains the engine of our stolen base strategy; despite a slight drag from Houser\u2019s elite pop-time against runners, the aggressive placement at the top of the order and the SP\u2019s high xERA make **Trea Turner** a lock to drive run production. **Kyle Schwarber** (70.37) also exploits that same Houser matchup, utilizing his elite xwOBA to capitalize on the favorable SP profile.\n\nThe middle of our lineup shows steady production, with **Colt Keith** (63.34) and **Kazuma Okamoto** (60.36) providing stability against mid-tier arms. **Carson Benge** (56.03) lands in the marginal category; he is our final active piece today, squeezed into the UTIL slot by the lack of depth on an off-day for the likes of **Junior Caminero**, **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, and **Caleb Durbin**. The benching of **Jerar Encarnacion** (39.39) was the most difficult decision, but the data is clear: facing S\u00e1nchez, whose xERA of 3.02 significantly suppresses raw output, drops **Jerar Encarnacion** just below our strictly enforced 40.0 efficiency floor. \n\nRisk management remains paramount as we navigate this slate. We are keeping a close watch on **Carson Benge**; while his matchup against Mikolas offers a decent SP skill advantage, his lower batting order position creates a volatility risk that could suppress his overall contribution. We continue to monitor the status of our depth pieces like **Christian Yelich**, **Hyeseong Kim**, **Zac Veen**, **Lars Nootbaar**, **Chase Meidroth**, **Gary Sanchez**, **Luke Raley**, **Josh Smith**, **Dillon Dingler**, **Pedro Ramirez**, and **Luis Pena** to ensure we maintain our competitive edge in the 5x5 categories as we look ahead to roster rotation later this week.",
